      <body>
         <head>To <persName>
                    <ptr target="../persons/pers0179">Ebenezer
               Blackwell</ptr>
                </persName>
                <note place="foot" n="1">
                    <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0179">Blackwell</ptr>
                    </persName> was apparently the
               friend with whom <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">Wesley</ptr>
                    </persName>
               had discussed his idea of <seg ana="military">a company of volunteers</seg> in <seg ana="war SevenYearsWar FrenchInvasion">the event of a French invasion</seg>, and
               who had agreed to handle <index indexName="works">
                        <term cRef="27:15-16">the
                     proposal</term>
                    </index> for him.</note>
            </head>
         <opener>
            <placeName>
               <district>Marlborough</district>
            </placeName>
            <lb/>
            <date when="1756-03-01">March 1, 1756</date>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>
            <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>I hope <index indexName="works">
                    <term cRef="27:15-16">the enclosed</term>
                </index> will
               do,<note place="foot" n="2">
                    <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">Wesley</ptr>
                    </persName> enclosed a fair copy of <index indexName="works">
                        <term cRef="27:15-16">his letter to <persName>
                                <ptr target="../persons/pers2198">James
                           West</ptr>
                            </persName> (see the following)</term>
                    </index>, which is why
               the charge to be paid by <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0179">Blackwell</ptr>
                    </persName> was sixpence instead of the threepence which would
               have been normal for a letter from
                  <placeName>
                        <district>Marlborough</district>
                    </placeName> to
                     <placeName>
                        <region>London</region>
                    </placeName>, under eighty
               miles.<!--Should this distance be tagged?-->
                </note> for I have not leisure to alter
            it any more.</p>
         <p>To make professions does not belong to me. It is quite foreign to my character. Let
            those who mean nothing <hi rend="italic">talk</hi>, like
               <!--Are these two character roles wrapped correctly? They are not *actual* people, so <persName> didn't seem correct.-->
                <role>Goneril</role>
                <note place="foot" n="3">Orig.,'Gonorill'.</note> and <role>Regan</role> in
                  <bibl>
                    <hi rend="italic">King Lear</hi>
                </bibl>.<note place="foot" n="4">See
                        <bibl>
                        <persName>
                            <ptr target="http://viaf.org/viaf/96994048">Shakespeare</ptr>
                        </persName>, <hi rend="italic">King Lear</hi>,
                  I.i.57–73.</bibl>
                </note> By <persName>God</persName>’s help, <seg ana="civilDuty">I will <hi rend="italic">do</hi> what a good subject ought</seg>.</p>
         <closer>Wishing <persName>
                    <ptr target="../persons/pers0180">Mrs. [Elizabeth]
                  Blackwell</ptr>
                </persName> and <persName>
                    <ptr target="../persons/pers0179">you</ptr>
                </persName>
            <seg ana="health">all health of soul and body</seg>, I am, dear sir, <signed>Your
               affectionate servant,<lb/>
               <persName>
                        <ptr target="../persons/pers0001">John Wesley</ptr>
                    </persName>
            </signed>
         </closer>
      </body>
      <p>
            <hi rend="italic">Address</hi>: 'To / <persName>
                <ptr target="../persons/pers0179">Mr
               Blackwell, <occupation>Banker</occupation>
                </ptr>
            </persName> / in /
               <placeName>
                <region>London</region>
            </placeName>'.</p>
